      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While tariffs can temporarily shield specific industries from foreign competition, they rarely offer a long-term solution for self-sufficiency because they distort markets and encourage inefficiency. Relying on protectionism often leads to higher prices for consumers and retaliatory measures from trading partners that hurt exports more than it helps domestic manufacturing. Ultimately, the best way to protect local jobs is through innovation and investment in worker training, not by artificially blocking global trade.",
      "source": "target",
