    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so you're basically saying there's no real downside to free trade and that protectionism is just an error? it feels like you're framing it as if the \"correct\" answer is always open markets, even when those markets are being gamed by countries with way lower standards and subsidized industries. is there actually any valid economic argument for using tariffs that isn't just \"inefficient\"?",
